<br>
So here is an idea that popped up during our discussion, any comments from you highlevels? I get Flux at 24, want to try to use it. Basically, if my 100 DD dont aggro a mob when cast twice in a row, why should my AE?<br>
<br>
Here goes, tactics idea : <br>
<br>
                  Tank (cleric)<br>
                   2 pet owners<br>
                   Whatever<br>
<br>
                   AE casters of course;<br>
<br>
Ok, puller runs around until he got 3 mobs on tail. Heads back to group. Everybody prepares real well, and try to target their correct target (I get to that).<br>
<br>
Puller stops, and starts tanking all 3 mobs. The 2 pet masters sic their pets on each their targets (They already selected each ones target during INC).Melee goes for 10 secs. Controlled AE burn from 3 casters. When I cast my best dd (1 of 97, it wont aggro a mob if I space it out. Same should apply to AEs, since your AE only builds aggro on your target in same fashion, you dont get 3x aggro PER mob.<br>
<br>
So, what would be the benefit : <br>
<br>
a) you utilize the healing of the pets, which is relatively big (from level 39 onwards). Also relatively good at lower levels.With 3 pets at 39 that would be over 100 HP heal per tic. Hell, the bad thing is that this healing is NOT USED most of the time today. Pffft!!! <br>
<br>
b) you cast AE spells that do 2,6 upwards damage per mana. Hell, at high levels we would talk 6 damage per mana. <br>
<br>
c) IF you overburn, the mob will come after you. But a pet will be on its tail! Use earth pet, or just have the chanter handy. (This should happen rarely if you get it right, need to rehearse of course).<br>
<br>
d) cleric would only need to heal up tank, which is being beaten by one mob only. Mana efficient?<br>
<br>
e) let one wizard toss in a DD at tanks mob, to finish that off relatively fast. <br>
<br>
 f) group saves a shitload of mana per damage.<br>
<br>
g) finally, the group would be able to kill 3 mobs in the time you usually kill one. And the casters would<br>
 have been using their mana and pet HPs so much more effectively.<br>
<br>
-------------------------------------<br>
 Drawbacks :<br>
<br>
a) you have 3 targets &quot;live&quot;, even if all are engaged in melee with tank/pets. <br>
<br>
 b) first mob will die slower<br>
<br>
c) you are more vulnerable to walk-in mobs. Hey, use the chanter for that! (Chanter only used if<br>
 overaggroed pet in above scenario).<br>
<br>
 -------------------------------------------------------<br>
What you all think? <br>
<br>
Final note : If the pets got beaten low, just do a standard one-mob pull next. The pets will be 100% and ready to go again when that single mob falls.<br>
