<br>
Puller with a lot of hit points.  Objective is to come back to the group with a minimum of 7 different experience mobs.<br>
<br>
Chanter with area of effect stuns.  Chain cast these over and over and over, non-stop until every mob is dead.<br>
<br>
Cleric with three roles.  Buff the puller to survive the pull, heal party members as required (ressurrect if the puller doesn't survive the pull), and perform as an AoE nuker.<br>
<br>
Three AoE nukers.  These nukers have to have a Point Blank Area of Effect nuke.  Rain spell is garbage as it only affects so many targets.  Clerics and Druids using Upheaval is great.  Any spell that has a moderate range, centered upon the caster, and can hit unlimited targets is the key.  <br>
<br>
The basic idea, most casters can inflict approximately 4/5th's their maximum single target nuke damage, using their AoE spells.  But from experience in Mistmoore (invis the puller, with instructions to enter castle and come back with the worst train he could pull), it is possible to consistently take out 12 or more blue experience mobs, for close to the same mana the group uses to take a single yellow mob.  As long as the tank can survive the pull, the group has the mana to take out 50 mobs; this is very fast leveling, with a little practice. <p><BR>
